name: 5-(carboxyamino)imidazole ribonucleotide synthase
comment: In Escherichia coli, this enzyme, along with EC 5.4.99.18, 5-(carboxyamino)imidazole ribonucleotide mutase, is required to carry out the single reaction catalysed by EC 4.1.1.21, phosphoribosylaminoimidazole carboxylase, in vertebrates. Belongs to the ATP grasp protein superfamily [3]. Carboxyphosphate is the putative acyl phosphate intermediate. Involved in the late stages of purine biosynthesis.
